1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:03,271
One machine, running at a fraction of what it can do.

2
00:00:03,271 --> 00:00:07,526
When compute sits idle, OneCompute quietly takes it back.

3
00:00:07,526 --> 00:00:11,183
Spare capacity, reclaimed, machine by machine.

4
00:00:11,183 --> 00:00:14,148
A single job, fanned out across the fleet.

5
00:00:14,148 --> 00:00:18,404
Thousands of idle cores, waking in parallel.

6
00:00:18,404 --> 00:00:22,859
Redirected, in an instant, to the work that matters most.

